R = \left\{ a + b \frac{1+ i \sqrt{3} }{2}: a,b \in \mathbb{Z} \right\}
z_1,z_2 \in R
z_1-z_2 \in R
z_1 \cdot z_2 \in R
N\left(a+b\frac{1+\sqrt-3}{2}\right)=a^2+ab+b^2
\frac{1+ i \sqrt{3} }{2}=-\omega \implies \omega^2=-\omega 
